{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "Artificial intelligence is the technology behind the tools that finish your sentences, recommend your next song, spot tumors in scans, and drive cars. This chapter shows what AI actually does, where it already lives in your day, and the surprising ideas that make it worth going deeper. You'll see what the field builds, why it matters for work and society, and the kinds of projects and roles people take on. The full course then takes you from these first impressions into how these systems really work.",
    "title": "What AI actually is"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "AI is software that learns patterns from examples instead of following rules a person wrote by hand. Show a system thousands of cat photos and it starts recognizing cats on its own. This lesson clarifies the difference between programming a computer and teaching one.",
      "title": "What AI really does"
    },
    {
      "description": "Your phone unlocking with your face, spam filters, product suggestions, voice assistants, map routes, and photo search are all AI at work. This lesson points out how many quiet decisions around you are already made by learning systems.",
      "title": "Where AI shows up in your day"
    },
    {
      "description": "A single model can write, translate, summarize, and answer questions without being separately programmed for each task. It learned language by predicting the next word billions of times. This lesson unpacks why that simple trick produces such flexible behavior.",
      "title": "The surprising power of predicting the next word"
    },
    {
      "description": "AI can be confidently wrong, absorb bias from its training data, and struggle with things a child finds easy. This lesson shows why knowing the limits matters as much as knowing the capabilities.",
      "title": "Where AI gets things wrong"
    },
    {
      "description": "People build AI as researchers, engineers, data specialists, and product designers, but also use it as artists, doctors, teachers, and hobbyists shipping small projects. This lesson maps realistic ways to get involved and what this course sets you up to do next.",
      "title": "Who works with AI and how you can start"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "A biologia é o estudo de tudo que está vivo, das bactérias invisíveis no seu intestino às florestas que respiram junto com o planeta. Neste capítulo você vai ver como a vida funciona por trás das cenas: como uma única célula vira um corpo inteiro, como plantas transformam luz em comida e como o mesmo código químico une você a uma baleia e a um cogumelo. Também vai descobrir onde essa área aparece no dia a dia, na medicina, na comida, no meio ambiente e na tecnologia, além de caminhos reais para quem quer seguir adiante. É um convite para olhar o mundo vivo com novos olhos antes de mergulhar no curso completo.",
    "title": "O mundo vivo por dentro"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "Da menor bactéria à maior árvore, a biologia procura entender o que diferencia o vivo do não vivo: crescer, reagir, se reproduzir e passar informação adiante. Veja como esse fio conecta seres tão diferentes.",
      "title": "O que torna algo vivo"
    },
    {
      "description": "Todo ser vivo é feito de células, e dentro delas acontecem reações incríveis o tempo todo. Uma única célula pode se multiplicar até formar um corpo inteiro com bilhões delas trabalhando em conjunto.",
      "title": "A célula, a fábrica invisível da vida"
    },
    {
      "description": "Plantas capturam luz do sol e a transformam em açúcar, liberando o oxigênio que você respira agora. Veja por que quase toda a energia da vida na Terra começa nesse truque silencioso.",
      "title": "Como a luz vira comida e ar"
    },
    {
      "description": "Vacinas, remédios, alimentos, saneamento e conservação da natureza nascem do conhecimento biológico. Perceba como decisões sobre saúde e meio ambiente dependem dessa ciência.",
      "title": "A biologia no seu dia a dia"
    },
    {
      "description": "Pesquisa em laboratório, saúde, agricultura, biotecnologia, ecologia de campo e educação são alguns dos rumos possíveis. Conheça comunidades e projetos onde quem gosta de vida pode atuar.",
      "title": "Caminhos para quem ama a vida"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "Quantum mechanics is the rulebook for how the smallest pieces of the universe—electrons, atoms, and light—actually behave, and the answers are stranger than fiction. This chapter shows you what the field studies, why it quietly powers your phone, medical scanners, and computers, and which ideas make physicists light up. You'll see where quantum thinking shows up in real life and what people build with it, so the full course feels like something worth continuing.",
    "title": "What Quantum Mechanics Is Really About"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "At tiny scales, particles don't sit in one clear spot with one clear speed. Instead, nature deals in probabilities, and things behave like both particles and waves. See what quantum mechanics actually describes and why the everyday rules stop working down there.",
      "title": "The world at its smallest scale"
    },
    {
      "description": "A single particle can act as if it takes many paths at once, and measuring it changes what you find. Meet superposition and the measurement puzzle—the ideas that made Einstein uneasy and still spark debate today.",
      "title": "How a particle can be in two states"
    },
    {
      "description": "Lasers, LEDs, MRI machines, solar cells, and the transistors inside every phone all rely on quantum behavior. See how these odd rules turned into technology you already use every day.",
      "title": "Where quantum shows up in daily life"
    },
    {
      "description": "Quantum computers, ultra-precise sensors, and secure communication are being built right now using these principles. Meet the researchers, engineers, and open communities working on them—and the kinds of projects you could follow.",
      "title": "What people are building with it"
    },
    {
      "description": "See how this course moves from strange first ideas toward the tools that make them precise, so each odd result starts to feel like something you can reason about instead of just memorize.",
      "title": "How this course takes you deeper"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "Before any courtroom drama, someone has to decide where a lawsuit can be filed, who gets sued, what evidence both sides must share, and how disputes end without a trial. Civil procedure is the rulebook that turns a private conflict into an orderly legal process. This chapter shows what these rules do, why they quietly decide the outcome of countless cases, and how mastering them gives lawyers real leverage. You'll see how procedure shapes everything from a neighbor dispute to a nationwide class action, and how the full course builds your command of the machinery behind every civil case.",
    "title": "How Lawsuits Actually Work"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "Civil procedure governs the non-criminal disputes between people, companies, and governments\\u2014contract fights, injuries, property claims, and more. It answers the practical questions: which court hears the case, when each side must act, and how the whole thing moves from complaint to resolution. It's the traffic system that keeps thousands of private conflicts from turning into chaos.",
      "title": "What Civil Procedure Governs"
    },
    {
      "description": "Cases are often won or lost on procedure long before anyone argues who was right. Filing in the wrong court, missing a deadline, or naming the wrong defendant can sink a strong claim. Lawyers who know the rules can shift a case to friendly ground, force early disclosure, or end a lawsuit before trial\\u2014turning fine print into strategy.",
      "title": "Why the Rules Decide Cases"
    },
    {
      "description": "Most lawsuits never reach a jury. They settle, get dismissed, or are resolved by motion. Procedure is what creates those off-ramps\\u2014pretrial deadlines, information exchange, and judicial screening that filter out weak claims and push both sides toward resolution. This is where the real work of the legal system happens.",
      "title": "How Cases End Without a Trial"
    },
    {
      "description": "Litigators, judges, clerks, and paralegals all live inside these rules every day, and so do people running class actions that affect millions. Knowing procedure well is a durable skill that travels across every area of law, from personal injury to corporate disputes. This course builds that command step by step, so the rulebook becomes a tool you can wield.",
      "title": "Where This Skill Takes You"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "Las ciudades no aparecen por accidente: alguien decidió dónde ponen las calles, los parques, las paradas de autobús y hasta el ancho de las banquetas. El urbanismo es el arte y la ciencia de dar forma a esos lugares donde vivimos. En este capítulo verás cómo pequeñas decisiones de diseño cambian tu día completo, por qué algunas ciudades se sienten vivas y otras vacías, y qué tipo de trabajo y proyectos hacen las personas que diseñan el espacio urbano. Es una mirada desde afuera antes de entrar de lleno al curso.",
    "title": "Cómo se piensa una ciudad"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "El urbanismo decide cómo se organizan las calles, viviendas, comercios y espacios públicos de un lugar. No se trata solo de edificios bonitos, sino de cómo se mueven, conviven y trabajan miles de personas al mismo tiempo. Aquí verás qué observa un urbanista cuando camina por una calle cualquiera.",
      "title": "Qué diseña realmente el urbanismo"
    },
    {
      "description": "Una banqueta más ancha, un cruce peatonal bien puesto o un árbol en la esquina cambian cuánta gente camina, se detiene y se siente segura. Verás cómo detalles casi invisibles deciden si una plaza se llena de vida o queda desierta.",
      "title": "Detalles pequeños que cambian una calle"
    },
    {
      "description": "El tiempo que tardas en llegar al trabajo, si tus hijos pueden ir solos a la escuela o si necesitas coche para todo dependen del diseño urbano. Aquí conectarás decisiones de planeación con tu rutina de cada día.",
      "title": "Cómo la ciudad decide tu día"
    },
    {
      "description": "Detrás de cada barrio hay planeadores, arquitectos, activistas vecinales, funcionarios y colectivos ciudadanos. Conocerás qué hace cada uno y cómo cualquier persona puede participar en cómo crece su ciudad.",
      "title": "Quiénes le dan forma a la ciudad"
    },
    {
      "description": "Este curso te llevará paso a paso desde cómo leer un mapa urbano hasta entender densidad, movilidad y espacio público. Aquí verás qué caminos abre y cómo cada capítulo suma para que veas tu ciudad con otros ojos.",
      "title": "Hacia dónde te lleva este curso"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "chapter": {
    "description": "Chaque œuvre d'art raconte une histoire : celle de la personne qui l'a créée, de l'époque qui l'a vue naître et des idées qui l'agitaient. L'histoire de l'art nous apprend à regarder une peinture, une sculpture ou une cathédrale et à comprendre ce qu'elles voulaient dire à leur public. Ce chapitre vous montre pourquoi ces objets fascinent encore et comment le cours vous donnera les clés pour les lire.",
    "title": "Regarder l'art autrement"
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "L'histoire de l'art ne juge pas si une œuvre est belle : elle demande pourquoi elle existe, pour qui elle a été faite et ce qu'elle révèle de son temps. Une même image peut être une prière, une propagande, une facture payée par un riche marchand. Vous verrez qu'une œuvre est toujours un message adressé à quelqu'un.",
      "title": "Ce que l'histoire de l'art cherche vraiment"
    },
    {
      "description": "Le dos de la Joconde, une couche de peinture cachée, un pigment plus cher que l'or : les œuvres gardent des secrets. Les rayons X révèlent des tableaux repeints, et un simple détail vestimentaire peut dater une scène à dix ans près. Une image contient bien plus que ce que l'œil saisit au premier regard.",
      "title": "Les indices cachés dans une œuvre"
    },
    {
      "description": "Vous croisez l'art partout : logos inspirés de fresques, films qui copient des cadrages de tableaux célèbres, affiches qui reprennent des couleurs de la Renaissance. Savoir lire l'art change votre façon de voir un musée, une ville ancienne ou même une publicité moderne.",
      "title": "L'art dans votre quotidien"
    },
    {
      "description": "Restauratrice de fresques, guide dans un musée, expert qui authentifie une toile, créateur de contenu sur l'art, chercheur qui reconstitue une époque : ce domaine mène à des métiers variés et à des communautés passionnées. Il existe aussi des projets ouverts à tous, comme documenter le patrimoine de sa région.",
      "title": "Les chemins que l'art peut ouvrir"
    }
  ]
}
